==English==
===Adjective===
'''binary''' (''not [[comparable]]'')

#Being in a state of one of two mutually exclusive conditions, such as on/off, true/false, the presence or absence of an electrical pulse.
#:Binary states are often abstracted as 1 and 0 in computer science.
#Concerning [[logic]] whose subject matter concerns binary states.
#(''mathematics, computing'') Concerning mathematical calculations performed using [[base]] 2.
#Having two equally-important parts,  e.g. a ''binary star system'' or a ''binary poison''; or related to something with two parts, e.g. the [[binary distribution]].

